<div class="container">
  <div class="header">
    <h1> Static Site Contact Form Service</h1>
    <p>Add contact forms to any static website without backend code</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Integration Instructions -->
  <div>
    <h2> How to Integrate</h2>

    <div>
      <div>
        <h4>1. Copy the Form</h4>
        <p>Copy the HTML form snippet below, You can apply css to style it to match your website design</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h4>2. Paste in Your Site</h4>
        <p>Add it to any HTML page on your static site</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h4>3. Set Your Site url and email address.</h4>
        <p>Replace "my-static-site" with your site name and "site_owner_email" with your email address to which the contact form submission notification will be sent.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h4>4. Done!</h4>
        <p>
          Your submissions can be viewed in "<%= @base_url %>/contact_submissions" page.
          Make sure you set your site url and site owner email correctly as shown in the following example.
          <br />
          <code>
            <%= @base_url %>/contact_submissions?site_owner_email=[SITE_OWNER_EMAIL]&site_url=[YOUR_WEBSITE_URL]
          </code>

          <br />
          <br />
          It might look something like this:
          <br />
          <code>
            <%= @base_url %>/contact_submissions?site_owner_email=some@email.com&site_url=http://localhost:4200
          </code>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- HTML Snippet Section -->
  <div>
    <h2> Copy-Paste Form Snippet</h2>
    <p>Add this contact form to your static website:</p>

    <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
      <pre>
<code>
  &lt;!-- Contact Form for Static Sites --&gt;
  &lt;form action="<%= @base_url %>/contact_submissions" method="POST"&gt;

    &lt;!-- Replace 'site_url' with your web address and 'site_owner_email' with your email address in the value attribute --&gt;
    &lt;input type="hidden" name="contact_submission[site_url]" value="site_url"&gt;
    &lt;input type="hidden" name="contact_submission[site_owner_email]" value="site_owner_email"&gt;

    &lt;div&gt;
      &lt;label for="name"&gt;Name:&lt;/label&gt;
      &lt;input type="text" id="name" name="contact_submission[name]" required&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;div&gt;
      &lt;label for="email"&gt;Email:&lt;/label&gt;
      &lt;input type="email" id="email" name="contact_submission[email]" required&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;div&gt;
      &lt;label for="message"&gt;Message:&lt;/label&gt;
      &lt;textarea id="message" name="contact_submission[message]" required&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;button type="submit"&gt; Send Message &lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/form&gt;
</code>
</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>